Reasoning: The paper challenges the common definition of Machine Learning as a subfield of AI and argues that meaningful information cannot be extracted from raw data sets. This suggests a focus on the theoretical foundations of Machine Learning, which is often discussed in the cs.AI sub-category. Additionally, the paper may touch on topics related to data processing and analysis, which are covered in the cs.LG and cs.CV sub-categories. The mention of "shared agreement and convention" among observers of data suggests a possible connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
